<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1923-03-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1923-03-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="221" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d221">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">868.48/414b: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1923-03-24T15:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">March 24,
                                        1923—3 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>50. Reports Department has received through Near East Relief indicate
                            that Turkish authorities have ordered deportation to interior of 4,500
                            refugees now at Mersina, in case arrangements are not made for their
                            immediate departure from that port.</p>
                        <p>See Department’s 44, March 16, 7 p.m. regarding refugees in
                            Constantinople and submit prompt telegraphic report regarding situation
                            there and at other Turkish ports.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>